<dl id="n12019o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12019o">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12019o"> 19(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Vikings speak to / Benedict through / Saxon dragoman <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12019o"><li>FW 486.08 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n12019o">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n12019o">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12019o">MS BL 47486a-100v</ms> </li><li>JJA 61:062 <a name="rAd10" href="../../FF/fdra/rda.htm#rAd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rA/rAd10.htm#n12019o">Draft: III&sect;3A.10</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">En l&apos;an 841, les b&eacute;n&eacute;dictins du Mont-Saint-Michel virent arriver une flottille de Normands. Les pirates abord&egrave;rent pour voir si ce rocher pourrait leur servir de retraite. Ils entr&egrave;rent en conversation avec les religieux, au moyen d&apos;un interpr&egrave;te saxon qu&apos;ils tra&icirc;naient avec eux et qui savait &agrave; peu pr&egrave;s toutes les langues du continent. <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 169</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: [In the year 841, the Benedictines of Mont-Saint-Michel saw a fleet of Normans arrive. The pirates landed to see if this rock could serve as a retreat. They entered in conversation with the religious, with the help of an interpreter whom they had with them and who knew almost all the languages of the continent.]  <br>Note: See also: <a name="n18240b" href="n18all.htm#n18240b">N18 (VI.B.8):240(b)</a>, possible source of <cite>FW</cite> 479.09. </mm> </mm></dd></dl>
